					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">This reminds me of the trick on some 8080/Z80/LR35902 machines (ZX Spectrum, MSX, Game Boy, and Master System/Game Gear, but not ColecoVision/SG-1000) to treat RAM as a 2D array, with the array index in H, the field offset in L, and different arrays using non-overlapping field offset ranges of the same pages. But I don't see it as quite as useful on 6502 because zero page access is only one cycle slower than transfers in and out of X and Y.</div>

