						<div class="postbody">That's an interesting concept. I've mostly been relying on having a few standard &quot;public&quot; subroutines that gameobjects expose to the outside, like update, collide, hurt, and death. My game engine calls them when the conditions are right (or every frame for update) along with some additional parameters about the situation.</div>

